name: AXON
description: An axon – derived from the Greek word meaning “axis’” – is a long slender nerve fiber  that conducts electrical impulses away from the nerve cell body. Like its sister piece  SYNAPSE – also editioned on Hicetnunc – AXON is an imagined neurological event derived from composite scans, motion stills, and digital painting. Created by Studio 3121 (Twitter: @Studio3121).
